Articles.Content:
So the turbojet texture in my install seems to be broken.

I know it is a mod doing this, but I'm not sure which. The files in my GameData folder are.

000_USITools

BoulderCo(E.V.E.)

BoxSat Alpha

CIT

CollisionFX

CommunityResourcePack

CrossFeedEnabler

DistantObject

EnviromentalVisualEnhancements(With Astronomer's Edge of Oblivion)

EternoRest2000

Firespitter(Plugin Only)

JSI

KAS

KerbalFoundries

KerbQuake

MechJeb2

ModuleRCSFX

MP_Nazari

NASAMission

ORSX

ProceduralFairings

SH_Mods(Mk2 IVA)

SmokeScreen

Squad

Tantares

TantaresLV

TextureReplacer

UmbraSpaceIndustries(ExpPack and SrvPack)

VNG

ModuleManager2.5.1

I am confident everything is up to date, so I'm not sure what is causing the issue.

Edited December 1, 2014 by mike9606
Your problem is coming from HotRockets. You can delete the I think it's called Emissives folder in MP_Nazari to give it the stock texture back.
That did fix the issue. Thanks for the help!
